{Local words.}                         
 loon=boy; tint=lost;scunner=hindrance;
 dinna=don't;                          
 biggin'=building;hasht=rushed;        
 taes=toes;muckle=many;puddocks=frogs; 
 ben=through; poke=paper bag;          
 girnie=grumbling; sark=shirt; gowk or 
 gype=stupid person; greet=weep;       
 tattie-bogie=scarecrow; loupit=leaped;
 simmit=vest; puckle=a few;            
 rousie=anger; doon=down; coo=cow;     
 sheltie=horse; beastie=insect;        
 chammer= a room; whaur=where;         
 barkit=dirty; reef=roof; sotter or    
 kirn=mess; pirn=reel of thread;       
 peer=poor; crater=child or piteous    
 person; pints=shoe-laces; nib=nose;   
 cloggies=sticks for burning;          
 estreen=yesterday; kirk=church;
